msContents.summary: Incomplete copy of an account of a pilgrimage to Mecca from North Africa in the early 18th century. The first leaf and a portion of the end are missing.

msItem.title: Riḥlat sayyid al-ṭarīqah wa-qaʻdat al-Sharīʻah wa-al-Ḥaqīqah
[رحلة سيد الطريقة وقعدة الشريعة والحقيقة]

author.persName: Ibn Nāṣir al-Darʻī, Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad, 1647-1717
ابن ناصر الدرعي، احمد بن محمد،

supportDesc.extent: i, 216, i paginated leaves : 215 x 160 (160 x 110) mm, bound to 230 x 180 x 50 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī script in brown ink; pointed.

origin.p: Copy completed by Maqdūd? ibn ʻUmar al-Ṣāyiqī (p. 427), perhaps in the later 18th or first half of the 19th century.

history.provenance: Purchased from Librairie orientaliste Paul Geuthner, circa 1908, with the Alexander I. Cotheal fund (library acquisition date stamp and name Geuthner in pencil f. 3r).
